type="user">erct-000L</fr:addr><fr:route>erct-000L.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="The univalence principle for precategories">The univalence principle for <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000B.xml"
addr="erct-000B"
title="Precategory">precategories</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000L.agda">erct-000L.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For any <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000B.xml"
addr="erct-000B"
title="Precategory">precategory</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex>, the type <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen D : \mathsf {Precategory}\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen D : \mathsf {Precategory}\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen D : \mathsf {Precategory}\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen D : \mathsf {Precategory}\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{D\cong  C}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000J.xml"
addr="erct-000J"
title="Isomorphism of precategories">isomorphisms of precategories</fr:link> onto <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001H.xml"
addr="erct-001H"
title="Contractible type">contractible</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>4345</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#358</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-358.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>The type of isomorphisms onto <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is inhabited, considering the identity isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{C}\colon  C\cong  C]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, it suffices to show that the type of <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000J.xml"
addr="erct-000J"
title="Isomorphism of precategories">isomorphisms</fr:link> onto <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> depicted below is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[    \begin {aligned}     D &: \mathsf {Precategory}\\     F &: D\cong  C    \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>We unfold the definitions of a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000B.xml"
addr="erct-000B"
title="Precategory">precategories</fr:link> and <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000J.xml"
addr="erct-000J"
title="Isomorphism of precategories">their isomorphisms</fr:link>, dropping <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">propositional</fr:link> axioms:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \begin {aligned}       D_0&: \mathsf {Type}\\       D_1&:D_0\to  D_0\to \mathsf {Set}\\       F_0&: D_0\to  C_0\\       F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }} D_1xy\to  C  \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_0x,F_0y\right \rparen \mathclose {} \\       h_1 &: \mathsf {isBiinvertible}\,F_0\\       h_2 &: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }} \mathsf {isPropMap}  \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_1xy\right \rparen \mathclose {}        \\       h_3 &: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }} \mathsf {isSurjection}  \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_1xy\right \rparen \mathclose {}      \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>A function that is both <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001T.xml"
addr="erct-001T"
title="N-truncated map">propositional</fr:link> and a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0029.xml"
addr="erct-0029"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link>, i.e. a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-003F.xml"
addr="erct-003F"
title="Bijection">bijection</fr:link>, is an <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000V.xml"
addr="erct-000V"
title="Equivalence of types">equivalence</fr:link> by <fr:ref
addr="erct-002Z"
href="erct-002Z.xml"
taxon="Corollary" />. We can therefore repackage our telescope equivalently:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \begin {aligned}       D_0&: \mathsf {Type}\\       D_1&:D_0\to  D_0\to \mathsf {Set}\\       F_0&: D_0\cong  C_0\\       F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {} }} D_1xy\cong  C  \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_0x,F_0y\right \rparen \mathclose {}      \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>By the univalence principle for types, we may contract 
 <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen D_0,F_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
 to 
 <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen   \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {} , 1_{  \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {} }\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \begin {aligned}       D_1&:  \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {} \to    \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {} \to \mathsf {Set}\\       F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {} }} D_1xy\cong  C  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\right \rparen \mathclose {}      \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>Next we rewrite using the univalence principles for functions and families of types (<fr:ref
addr="erct-0015"
href="erct-0015.xml"
taxon="Axiom" />, <fr:ref
addr="erct-001D"
href="erct-001D.xml"
taxon="Axiom" />):</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \begin {aligned}       D_1&:  \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {} \to    \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {} \to \mathsf {Set}\\       F_1&: D_1 = \lambda {x,y}\mathpunct {.}{C  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\right \rparen \mathclose {} }     \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>By the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0015.xml"
addr="erct-0015"
title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for functions</fr:link>, the data above is <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001H.xml"
addr="erct-001H"
title="Contractible type">contractible</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
